<p>The company was a legal entity by the summer of 2016, some half-year after its conceptual inception. And by the early winter of 2017, my partner and friend had lost interest in the vision and the idea of the venture.</p>

<p>I was left to finish up old contracts and did so, but Arthem hasn't taken on any new clients in a while. Efforts to find a partner to replace my quasi-co-founder haven't yielded anyone, and that's largely due to stagnation on what Arthem has been up to.</p>

<p>I share interesting technology news and art over facebook under that name, but not much else. The site was never completed, but I'm going to get to it soon enough.</p>

<p> Arthem.co lives here <a href="https://arthem.co">here</a> and I invite you to discover it for yourselves.</p>